And in one of life's little ironies,

5
01:09:53,980 --> 01:09:56,890
the son went to work for
the government whose betrayal

6
01:09:57,360 --> 01:10:00,770
caused the father to kill
himself and his wife.

7
01:10:01,180 --> 01:10:06,280
Hence Janus, the two-faced
Roman god, come to life.

8
01:10:06,370 --> 01:10:08,490
It wasn't God who gave me this face.

9
01:10:09,520 --> 01:10:12,730
It was you, setting the timers
for three minutes instead of six.

10
01:10:13,030 --> 01:10:18,960
- Am I supposed to feel sorry for you?
- No. You're supposed to die for me.

11
01:10:21,380 --> 01:10:22,590
By the way,

12
01:10:23,970 --> 01:10:28,150
I did think of asking you to join
my little scheme, but somehow I knew

13
01:10:29,070 --> 01:10:34,180
007's loyalty was always to the mission,
never to his friend.

14
01:10:36,280 --> 01:10:38,400
Closing time, James. Last call.

15
01:10:54,600 --> 01:10:55,770
For England, James.

16
01:10:56,070 --> 01:10:57,360
Wake up. Mister.

17
01:11:01,400 --> 01:11:04,220
Wake up, please. Wake up.

18
01:11:04,270 --> 01:11:06,480
I'm heard. I'm heard.

19
01:11:06,970 --> 01:11:08,830
Hurry. Hurry up. Come on.

20
01:11:11,030 --> 01:11:12,390
Pull yourself together or we're gonna die.

21
01:11:15,950 --> 01:11:19,410
- Do something. Get us out of here.
- I'm a little tied up.

22
01:11:20,280 --> 01:11:21,420
Never mind.

23
01:12:40,380 --> 01:12:43,450
The things we do
for frequent-flier mileage.

24
01:12:45,220 --> 01:12:47,020
Here. Let me help you.

25
01:12:47,490 --> 01:12:50,030
That's it. Mind your head.

26
01:12:57,970 --> 01:12:59,150
Let me go.

27
01:13:43,540 --> 01:13:44,430
Who are you ?

28
01:13:47,730 --> 01:13:51,270
- Listen. I'm on your side.
- I don't know anything.

29
01:13:51,450 --> 01:13:53,440
- I don't believe you.
- I don't care.

30
01:13:53,800 --> 01:13:55,110
Look, they might be back any minute.

31
01:13:55,180 --> 01:13:59,730
Are you with me, or your countrymen
who killed everyone at Severnaya ?

32
01:13:59,960 --> 01:14:01,610
I've never been to Severnaya.

33
01:14:02,470 --> 01:14:04,960
Your watch has. Frozen
by the GoldenEye blast.

34
01:14:06,090 --> 01:14:09,960
And I'm willing to bet you're the one
who climbed up the dish to get out.

35
01:14:11,320 --> 01:14:14,030
- Who are you ?
- I work for the British government.

36
01:14:14,200 --> 01:14:16,620
The more you tell me,
the more I can help you.

37
01:14:16,980 --> 01:14:21,270
- But I don't know anything.
- Then start with what you do know.

38
01:14:31,040 --> 01:14:32,310
My name is Natalya Simonova.

39
01:14:34,220 --> 01:14:36,590
I was a systems programmer
at Severnaya facility until...

40
01:14:38,250 --> 01:14:39,450
Go on.

41
01:14:41,190 --> 01:14:44,300
- ...until they killed everyone.
- Who ? Alec Trevelyan ?

42
01:14:45,460 --> 01:14:49,180
- No. I don't know who that is.
- Who's the insider ? Who's the traitor ?

43
01:14:49,850 --> 01:14:51,460
Boris. Boris Grishenko.

44
01:14:52,230 --> 01:14:54,460
- KGB or military?
- Computer programmer.

45
01:14:56,030 --> 01:14:58,470
- There was no one else ?
- No.

46
01:15:00,970 --> 01:15:02,820
They're going to kill me, aren't they ?

47
01:15:05,300 --> 01:15:07,200
Trust me.

48
01:15:08,310 --> 01:15:12,600
Trust you ? I don't even know your name.

49
01:15:14,000 --> 01:15:16,960
Good morning, Mr Bond. Sit.

50
01:15:23,900 --> 01:15:26,440
I am Defence Minister Dimitri Mishkin.

51
01:15:27,610 --> 01:15:29,990
So, by what means shall we
execute you, Commander Bond ?

52
01:15:30,460 --> 01:15:32,540
What, no small talk ?

53
01:15:32,960 --> 01:15:34,370
No chitchat ?

54
01:15:35,370 --> 01:15:39,080
That's the trouble. No one has time to do
a really sinister interrogation any more.

55
01:15:40,240 --> 01:15:43,080
- It's a lost art.
- Your sense of humour doesn't slay me.

56
01:15:44,250 --> 01:15:46,750
- Where is the GoldenEye ?
- I assumed you had it.

57
01:15:47,310 --> 01:15:49,460
I have an English spy,
a programmer and a helicopter...

58
01:15:50,020 --> 01:15:53,130
- That's how your traitor wants it to look.
- Who attacked Severnaya ?

59
01:15:53,290 --> 01:15:56,920
- Who had the codes ?
- The penalty for terrorism is still death.

60
01:15:57,090 --> 01:16:01,250
- And for treason ?
- Stop it, both of you. Stop it.

61
01:16:01,520 --> 01:16:03,840
You're like boys with toys.

62
01:16:09,540 --> 01:16:12,220
It was Ourumov.
General Ourumov set off the weapon.

63
01:16:12,590 --> 01:16:14,600
I saw him do it.

64
01:16:17,180 --> 01:16:19,510
- Are you certain it was Ourumov?
- Yes.

65
01:16:20,680 --> 01:16:23,600
He killed everyone,
then stole the GoldenEye.

66
01:16:24,450 --> 01:16:27,240
And why would he do that ?

67
01:16:28,510 --> 01:16:30,310
There is another satellite.

68
01:16:34,440 --> 01:16:35,650
Another GoldenEye.

69
01:16:37,690 --> 01:16:39,440
Thank you, Miss Simonova.

70
01:16:40,610 --> 01:16:42,980
What did you say about
the lost art of interrogation, Mr Bond ?

71
01:16:45,650 --> 01:16:48,820
Defence Minister, I must protest.
This is my investigation.

72
01:16:48,990 --> 01:16:51,070
You are out of order.

73
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:55,160
From what I am hearing,
it is you who is out of order.

74
01:16:56,320 --> 01:16:57,620
I've seen this gun
in the hand of our enemy.

75
01:16:57,960 --> 01:17:01,990
- Put it down, General.
- Do you even know who the enemy is ?

76
01:17:03,160 --> 01:17:04,950
- Do you ?
- Guard.

77
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:14,740
Defence Minister Dimitri Mishkin,

78
01:17:15,090 --> 01:17:19,170
murdered by British agent James Bond,

79
01:17:21,880 --> 01:17:24,500
himself shot while trying to escape.

80
01:17:25,470 --> 01:17:26,470
Guards.

81
01:17:38,650 --> 01:17:39,730
Come on.

82
01:18:20,440 --> 01:18:21,490
They're in the archive.

83
01:18:26,370 --> 01:18:28,000
Down.

84
01:19:19,630 --> 01:19:21,450
Spread out. Cover the other side.

85
01:19:22,760 --> 01:19:23,740
Trust me.

86
01:20:00,140 --> 01:20:01,140
Go now.

87
01:20:32,940 --> 01:20:33,460
Faster.

88
01:20:55,070 --> 01:20:55,610
Damn it.

89
01:21:03,170 --> 01:21:04,430
Down the alley.

90
01:22:05,070 --> 01:22:06,010
Use the bumper. That's what it's for.

91
01:22:06,580 --> 01:22:07,650
Nazad.

92
01:23:44,150 --> 01:23:45,550
What was that ?

93
01:24:23,220 --> 01:24:24,500
Go left.

94
01:25:04,330 --> 01:25:05,830
Get out.

95
01:25:58,650 --> 01:26:03,230
Either you've brought me the perfect gift,
or you've made me a very unhappy man.

96
01:26:04,270 --> 01:26:06,420
Mishkin got to them before I could.

97
01:26:07,420 --> 01:26:09,150
Bond is alive ?

98
01:26:10,840 --> 01:26:13,300
- He escaped.
- Good for Bond.

99
01:26:14,970 --> 01:26:16,410
Bad for you.

100
01:26:19,600 --> 01:26:20,710
Take a seat, my dear.

101
01:26:38,740 --> 01:26:40,380
You know, James and I
shared everything.

102
01:26:43,250 --> 01:26:44,640
Absolutely everything.

103
01:26:51,010 --> 01:26:52,270
To the victor go the spoils.

104
01:27:02,510 --> 01:27:03,630
You'll like it where we're going.

105
01:27:10,760 --> 01:27:12,170
You may even learn to like me.

106
01:27:22,550 --> 01:27:23,650
Stay with her.

107
01:27:30,860 --> 01:27:32,700
Bond. Only Bond.

108
01:27:33,550 --> 01:27:35,530
He's going to derail us.

109
01:27:37,080 --> 01:27:38,200
Full speed.

110
01:27:39,430 --> 01:27:41,380
Full speed. Ram him.

111
01:28:45,960 --> 01:28:49,160
Why can't you just
be a good boy and die ?

112
01:28:49,790 --> 01:28:50,610
You first.

113
01:28:51,600 --> 01:28:52,350
You second.

114
01:28:56,110 --> 01:28:57,150
Up.

115
01:28:59,640 --> 01:29:02,980
Situation analysis: hopeless.

116
01:29:03,390 --> 01:29:05,430
You have no backup, no escape route.

117
01:29:05,800 --> 01:29:09,140
And I have the only bargaining chip.

118
01:29:09,520 --> 01:29:14,810
- Where is she ?
- Ah, yes. Your fatal weakness.

119
01:29:15,060 --> 01:29:18,290
Ourumov, bring her in.

120
01:29:20,030 --> 01:29:21,540
Lovely girl.

121
01:29:23,010 --> 01:29:26,400
Tastes like... like strawberries.

122
01:29:27,060 --> 01:29:29,590
- I wouldn't know.
- I would.

123
01:29:37,350 --> 01:29:39,120
So, back where we started, James.

124
01:29:40,430 --> 01:29:42,160
Your friend, or the mission ?

125
01:29:43,430 --> 01:29:45,770
Drop the gun. I'll let her live.

126
01:29:49,300 --> 01:29:53,900
Ourumov, what has
this Cossack promised you ?

127
01:29:55,090 --> 01:29:58,390
You knew, didn't you ?
He's a Lienz Cossack.

128
01:29:58,800 --> 01:30:03,190
- It's in the past.
- He'll betray you. Just like everyone else.

129
01:30:04,050 --> 01:30:06,440
- Is this true ?
- What's true is that in 48 hours

130
01:30:06,690 --> 01:30:09,370
you and I will have more money than God.

131
01:30:09,960 --> 01:30:12,950
and Mr Bond here will have
a small memorial service

132
01:30:13,540 --> 01:30:16,820
with only Moneypenny and a few
tearful restaurateurs in attendance.

133
01:30:19,220 --> 01:30:21,450
So, what's the choice, James ?

134
01:30:22,400 --> 01:30:25,870
Two targets, time enough for one shot.

135
01:30:26,960 --> 01:30:28,580
The girl, or the mission ?

136
01:30:29,580 --> 01:30:32,210
Kill her. She means nothing to me.

137
01:30:34,680 --> 01:30:36,980
Kill her. She means nothing to me.

138
01:30:48,250 --> 01:30:51,470
- One-inch armour plating.
- I'm fine, thank you very much !

139
01:30:57,430 --> 01:30:59,050
Boris. Yes.

140
01:31:00,010 --> 01:31:03,450
- What are you doing ?
- Boris is on-line backing up his files.

141
01:31:03,960 --> 01:31:06,880
If I can spike him, I might be able
to find out where they're going.

142
01:31:09,760 --> 01:31:13,390
- Don't stand there. Get us out of here.
- Yes, sir.

143
01:31:32,420 --> 01:31:33,580
Good luck with the floor, James.

144
01:31:34,110 --> 01:31:37,720
I set the timers for six minutes
the same six minutes you gave me.

145
01:31:38,670 --> 01:31:40,370
It was the least I could do for a friend.

146
01:31:43,540 --> 01:31:46,040
- What does that mean ?
- We've got three minutes.

147
01:32:21,480 --> 01:32:23,480
- What else do you call your bottom ?
- What ?

148
01:32:22,900 --> 01:32:26,880
Boris' password. He plays word games.
"What I sit on but don't take with me".

149
01:32:27,520 --> 01:32:28,850
- Chair.
- Like I said...

150
01:32:34,570 --> 01:32:35,730
30 seconds.

151
01:32:36,000 --> 01:32:38,880
He's not in Russia,
Germany, Paris, London, Madrid...

152
01:32:39,460 --> 01:32:42,020
- 25 seconds.
- New York, Toronto, Chicago,

153
01:32:42,340 --> 01:32:43,960
- San Francisco...
- 20 seconds.

154
01:32:44,500 --> 01:32:46,660
Mexico City, Rio, Miami...

155
01:32:46,980 --> 01:32:55,830
- Come on.
- Wait. He's in Cuba. Havana... No.

156
01:32:58,110 --> 01:32:59,170
Now.

157
01:33:18,660 --> 01:33:20,870
Do you destroy
every vehicle you get into ?

158
01:33:21,320 --> 01:33:23,470
Standard operating procedure.

159
01:33:25,810 --> 01:33:27,070
Boys with toys.

160
01:33:30,980 --> 01:33:33,910
Maybe I should take care of
the transportation for our trip to Cuba.

161
01:33:34,330 --> 01:33:36,970
Our trip ?

162
01:33:37,650 --> 01:33:39,230
Do you know how to disarm the weapon ?

163
01:33:40,710 --> 01:33:46,280
I suppose that depends on what kind of
weapon you're talking about disarming.

164
01:33:48,550 --> 01:33:56,650
So, tell me. Are there any other
standard operating procedures

165
01:33:56,970 --> 01:33:59,360
I should be aware of, Commander ?
661
01:34:02,943 --> 01:34:03,986
Thousands.

166
01:34:05,430 --> 01:34:07,320
But I only pay them

167
01:34:08,030 --> 01:34:09,640
lip service.

168
01:34:32,990 --> 01:34:35,440
My whole life I dreamed
about coming to the Caribbean.

169
01:34:36,830 --> 01:34:37,960
It's so beautiful.

170
01:34:39,050 --> 01:34:40,530
Not another human being in sight.

171
01:34:54,210 --> 01:34:56,390
What is it with you and moving vehicles ?

172
01:35:22,000 --> 01:35:26,990
Yo, Jimbo. Brought a little gift
from old whatshisname ? T ? Z ?

173
01:35:27,230 --> 01:35:29,170
- Q.
- Yeah.

174
01:35:29,480 --> 01:35:32,440
- What are you doing here, Wade?
- Banyan trees.

175
01:35:32,940 --> 01:35:35,420
I am not here. The CIA has
no knowledge, no involvement.

176
01:35:35,710 --> 01:35:38,050
Nothing to do with your insertion
into Cuba, if you catch my drift.

177
01:35:38,360 --> 01:35:40,150
Yes, I do.

178
01:35:40,370 --> 01:35:43,060
Borrowed the plane
from a friend in the DEA.

179
01:35:45,790 --> 01:35:48,080
The Coast Guard and the FAA
are in the loop.

180
01:35:48,250 --> 01:35:50,920
You're cleared on our radar
for 06:00 hours.

181
01:35:51,040 --> 01:35:53,380
Here's the latest sat-int from Langley.

182
01:35:53,540 --> 01:35:57,250
- Stay below 600 feet.
- 500 feet.

183
01:35:57,420 --> 01:35:59,920
- Who's that ?
- Natalya Simonova.

184
01:36:00,090 --> 01:36:03,090
- Sim-yo-nova.
- Russian minister of transportation.

185
01:36:06,380 --> 01:36:08,680
Did you check her out ?

186
01:36:08,840 --> 01:36:12,720
- Head to toe.
- Right...

187
01:36:13,470 --> 01:36:17,560
So, you're lookin' for a dish the size
of a football field, huh ? Doesn't exist.

188
01:36:17,720 --> 01:36:21,230
- Light a cigar in Cuba and we see it.
- I know it's there.

189
01:36:21,390 --> 01:36:26,230
It's a duplicate of Severnaya, like
your secret transmitters in New Zealand.

190
01:36:26,390 --> 01:36:29,150
I've never been there.
How does she know about that ?

191
01:36:29,310 --> 01:36:34,020
- What if I need backup ?
- Get on the radio. I'll send in the marines.

192
01:36:34,610 --> 01:36:36,980
Anyway, hang a left
at the end of the runway.

193
01:36:37,150 --> 01:36:40,150
- Cuba's 80 miles on your right.
- Yo, Wade.

194
01:36:44,030 --> 01:36:47,320
Just one thing. Don't push
any of the buttons on that car.

195
01:36:47,490 --> 01:36:50,870
- I'm just gonna bomb around in it.
- Exactly.

196
01:36:51,620 --> 01:36:54,330
Yo, James. I got faith, but be careful.

197
01:36:54,490 --> 01:36:57,160
He knows you're comin'.

198
01:37:59,290 --> 01:38:01,400
He was your friend - Trevelyan.

199
01:38:03,810 --> 01:38:05,990
And now he's your enemy
and you will kill him.

200
01:38:08,220 --> 01:38:10,570
It is that simple ?

201
01:38:12,120 --> 01:38:13,980
In a word, yes.

202
01:38:15,460 --> 01:38:17,700
- Unless he kills you first.
- Natalya...

203
01:38:17,950 --> 01:38:21,810
You think I'm impressed? With your guns,
your killing, your death. For what ?

204
01:38:22,920 --> 01:38:24,240
So you can be a hero ?

205
01:38:26,480 --> 01:38:27,480
- All the heroes I know are dead.
- Natalya...

206
01:38:28,450 --> 01:38:31,950
How can you act like this ?
How can you be so cold ?

207
01:38:34,410 --> 01:38:36,150
It's what keeps me alive.

208
01:38:38,270 --> 01:38:41,290
No. It's what keeps you alone.

209
01:39:20,760 --> 01:39:21,820
James...

210
01:39:24,370 --> 01:39:24,840
Yes ?

211
01:39:32,810 --> 01:39:33,790
On the train,

212
01:39:35,970 --> 01:39:40,040
when you told him to kill me
and that I meant nothing to you,

213
01:39:40,460 --> 01:39:42,140
did you mean it ?

214
01:39:44,450 --> 01:39:45,000
Yes.

215
01:39:47,330 --> 01:39:50,290
Basic rule: always call their bluff.

216
01:39:55,850 --> 01:39:56,400
No.

217
01:40:29,900 --> 01:40:33,810
Turn ten degrees south, bearing 1-8-4.

218
01:40:34,440 --> 01:40:35,280
Yes, sir.

219
01:41:00,840 --> 01:41:02,870
Nothing. There is nothing here.

220
01:41:04,710 --> 01:41:06,010
Let's make another pass.

221
01:41:20,050 --> 01:41:22,400
Maybe Wade was right. There is no dish.

222
01:42:21,160 --> 01:42:21,990
Natalya.

223
01:43:22,950 --> 01:43:27,560
This time, Mr Bond,
the pleasure will be all mine.

224
01:43:46,410 --> 01:43:48,740
You wait for your turn.

225
01:44:22,950 --> 01:44:24,830
She always did enjoy a good squeeze.

226
01:44:36,770 --> 01:44:39,750
- Is the satellite in range?
- Six minutes.

227
01:44:40,150 --> 01:44:42,710
- Prepare the dish.
- No. It's too early.

228
01:44:43,450 --> 01:44:45,450
- I am not ready.
- Do it.

229
01:45:17,100 --> 01:45:18,260
No wonder we couldn't see it.

230
01:45:29,430 --> 01:45:30,960
Come on.

231
01:45:46,860 --> 01:45:48,330
The world's greatest cash card.

232
01:45:50,320 --> 01:45:52,490
It had better not be rejected.

233
01:46:57,010 --> 01:46:59,600
- Mischa is on-line.
- Sir.

234
01:47:05,780 --> 01:47:06,490
Kill him.

235
01:47:08,160 --> 01:47:09,750
The man just won't take a hint.

236
01:47:11,880 --> 01:47:15,810
- Target coordinates ?
- The target is London.

237
01:47:28,570 --> 01:47:30,010
He's getting ready to signal the satellite.

238
01:47:31,600 --> 01:47:33,950
- How do you stop it ?
- The transmitter above the antenna.

239
01:48:06,200 --> 01:48:07,950
Antenna in position.

240
01:48:10,840 --> 01:48:12,490
On my count.

241
01:48:13,550 --> 01:48:17,460
Three, two, one.

242
01:48:46,260 --> 01:48:47,450
God save the Queen.

243
01:49:07,440 --> 01:49:10,080
- The mainframe computer.
- Don't move.

244
01:50:37,510 --> 01:50:40,280
James. What an unpleasant surprise.

245
01:50:40,920 --> 01:50:42,970
- We aim to please.
- Where's the girl ?

246
01:50:44,700 --> 01:50:45,390
Find her.

247
01:50:53,020 --> 01:50:54,600
So, how is old Q ?

248
01:50:55,880 --> 01:50:57,420
Up to his usual tricks ?

249
01:50:59,260 --> 01:51:00,150
The watch.

250
01:51:06,540 --> 01:51:09,690
A new model. Still press here, do I ?

251
01:51:27,030 --> 01:51:28,740
Interesting setup, Alec.

252
01:51:29,910 --> 01:51:32,360
You break into the Bank of England
via computer,

253
01:51:32,750 --> 01:51:34,320
then transfer the money electronically

254
01:51:35,390 --> 01:51:37,620
just seconds before
you set off the GoldenEye,

255
01:51:38,610 --> 01:51:40,830
which erases any record
of the transactions.

256
01:51:42,510 --> 01:51:44,870
- Ingenious.
- Thank you, James.

257
01:51:45,660 --> 01:51:47,580
But it still boils down to petty theft.

258
01:51:49,260 --> 01:51:53,610
In the end, you're just a bank robber.
Nothing more than a common thief.

259
01:52:04,380 --> 01:52:06,120
You always did have
a small mind, James.

260
01:52:07,170 --> 01:52:11,400
It's not just erasing bank records. It's
everything on every computer in London.

261
01:52:12,280 --> 01:52:16,950
Tax records, the stock market,
credit ratings, land registries,

262
01:52:17,230 --> 01:52:18,360
criminal records.

263
01:52:18,560 --> 01:52:23,550
In 16 minutes and 43... no, 42 seconds,,

264
01:52:24,260 --> 01:52:26,070
the United Kingdom
will re-enter the Stone Age.

265
01:52:26,720 --> 01:52:28,700
A worldwide financial meltdown.

266
01:52:30,000 --> 01:52:34,290
And all so mad little Alec can settle
a score with the world 50 years on.

267
01:52:34,620 --> 01:52:39,200
Please, James. Spare me the Freud.
I might as well ask you

268
01:52:39,440 --> 01:52:42,270
if all the vodka martinis ever silence
the screams of all the men you've killed.

269
01:52:46,360 --> 01:52:48,370
Or if you find forgiveness
in the arms of all those willing women

270
01:52:48,660 --> 01:52:52,000
for all the dead ones
you failed to protect.

271
01:52:54,890 --> 01:52:57,330
England is about to learn
the cost of betrayal,

272
01:52:58,460 --> 01:53:00,760
inflation-adjusted for 1945.

273
01:53:03,880 --> 01:53:06,630
- Welcome to the party, my dear.
- Natalya.

274
01:53:41,280 --> 01:53:45,080
Don't ever do that again.

275
01:53:45,340 --> 01:53:48,470
This is not one of your games, Boris.
Real people will die.

276
01:53:48,840 --> 01:53:50,670
You pathetic little worm.

277
01:53:52,620 --> 01:53:54,560
She was in the mainframe.
Check the computer.

278
01:53:55,160 --> 01:53:59,000
She's a moron.
A second-level programmer.

279
01:53:59,640 --> 01:54:01,850
She works on the guidance system.

280
01:54:02,770 --> 01:54:05,860
She doesn't even have access
to the firing codes.

281
01:54:10,360 --> 01:54:11,800
Retro-rockets firing.

282
01:54:31,090 --> 01:54:35,960
- What the hell's happening ?
- We will have re-entry in 12 minutes.

283
01:54:38,340 --> 01:54:40,880
It will burn up
somewhere over the Atlantic.

284
01:54:41,050 --> 01:54:44,730
- Deal with it.
- She changed the access codes.

285
01:54:45,140 --> 01:54:47,050
Then she can fix it.

286
01:54:51,630 --> 01:54:54,990
Go ahead. Shoot him.
He means nothing to me.

287
01:54:56,230 --> 01:54:58,950
I can do it. I can break her codes.

288
01:54:59,460 --> 01:55:01,590
Then get on with it.

289
01:55:29,960 --> 01:55:31,360
Tell him. Now.

290
01:55:32,260 --> 01:55:35,960
Give me the codes, Natalya.
Give them to me.

291
01:55:51,570 --> 01:55:54,260
- Can Boris break your codes ?
- Possibly.

292
01:55:54,420 --> 01:55:55,760
Possibly ?

293
01:55:57,180 --> 01:55:58,860
We have to destroy the transmitter.

294
01:55:59,920 --> 01:56:02,250
By the way, I'm fine,
thank you very much !

295
01:56:31,730 --> 01:56:32,780
Do you know how to use one of these ?

296
01:56:35,570 --> 01:56:36,640
Yes.

297
01:56:38,360 --> 01:56:40,200
Good. Stay out of sight.

298
01:56:55,300 --> 01:56:56,540
- How long ?
- Two minutes.

299
01:56:57,420 --> 01:56:59,070
- One minute.
- Guard.

300
01:56:59,520 --> 01:57:02,780
- I'm fixing it.
- If he moves, kill him.

301
01:58:26,130 --> 01:58:29,210
Yes. I am invincible.

302
02:00:39,780 --> 02:00:42,780
You know, James ?

303
02:00:42,950 --> 02:00:44,820
I was always better.

304
02:01:02,000 --> 02:01:03,130
Alpha One to Gunship.

305
02:01:04,250 --> 02:01:06,750
Alpha One to Gunship.

306
02:02:07,410 --> 02:02:09,200
Speak to me.

307
02:02:44,350 --> 02:02:46,390
For England, James ?

308
02:02:47,100 --> 02:02:48,470
No.

309
02:02:49,430 --> 02:02:50,810
For me.

310
02:04:10,140 --> 02:04:12,560
Yes. I am invincible.

311
02:04:37,400 --> 02:04:40,860
James. James. Are you all right ?

312
02:04:44,830 --> 02:04:47,120
Yes, I'm fine. Thank you.

313
02:04:57,290 --> 02:04:59,960
Suppose someone is watching ?

314
02:05:01,040 --> 02:05:04,580
There's no one within 25 miles,
believe me.

315
02:05:04,750 --> 02:05:07,130
Yo, Jimbo.

316
02:05:15,670 --> 02:05:19,970
Is this supposed to be your idea
of "coming through in a clinch" ?

317
02:05:21,680 --> 02:05:23,930
It's tobacco plants.

318
02:05:24,100 --> 02:05:25,970
I said I'd be here, huh ?

319
02:05:26,140 --> 02:05:28,350
Yo. Marines.

320
02:05:38,480 --> 02:05:43,940
Maybe you two'd like to finish debriefing
each other at Guantanamo ?

321
02:05:44,610 --> 02:05:47,190
- Ready ?
- I'm not going on a helicopter with you.

322
02:05:47,360 --> 02:05:50,320
No plane, no train, nothing that moves.

323
02:05:50,480 --> 02:05:53,860
Darling, what could
possibly go wrong, hey ?

